SENATE BILL 267
L6, Q2, Q6 6lr1390
By: Senator Brooks
Introduced and read first time: January 19, 2026
Assigned to: Education, Energy, and the Environment and Budget and Taxation
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
Senate action: Adopted
Read second time: March 2, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Land Use – Residential Housing – Oversight, Regulation, and Taxation and
3 Approval
4 (Building Affordably in My Back Yard Act)
5 FOR the purpose of establishing certain policies and processes to facilitate the development
6 of residential housing in the State; requiring an entity that owns residential real
7 property in the State to make a certain certification to the Department of Housing
8 and Community Development; authorizing a local jurisdiction to establish an
9 administrative process to review, approve, modify, or deny certain housing
10 development project applications; requiring certain local jurisdictions and the
11 Maryland–National Capital Park and Planning Commission to establish processes
12 to evaluate the completeness of residential or mixed–use development project
13 applications; specifying the standards applicable to certain complete and approved
14 development project applications; providing for the establishment of certain housing
15 production targets; requiring certain local jurisdictions and the Commission to adopt
16 local project design guidelines for certain qualified affordable housing projects;
17 requiring local jurisdictions and the Commission to implement certain pre–approval
18 building permit application processes for standardized model home designs;
19 authorizing a county to reduce the fee or tax rate of certain housing–sensitive taxes
20 or fees imposed on a qualified affordable housing project; authorizing a county to
21 increase the fee or tax rate of certain housing–sensitive taxes or fees on classes of
22 property that are not part of a qualified affordable housing project; allowing a county
23 or municipality to require the payment of a certain percentage of certain
24 development excise taxes and development impact fees before a housing development
25 project is completed; limiting the entities from which a certain person may accept
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
