amendment. *sb0267*

2 SENATE BILL 267
1 offers on residential real property during a certain period of time; authorizing a
2 county, after making a certain determination, to impose a transfer tax on the
3 transfer of certain owner–occupied properties; authorizing the Mayor and City
4 Council of Baltimore or the governing body of a county to establish, by law, certain
5 subclasses of real property and to set a special property tax rate for the subclasses
6 of real property; requiring the Comptroller, in consultation with the State
7 Department of Assessments and Taxation, to evaluate and report on disincentives to
8 homeowners to downsize or transition to smaller homes; requiring the Department
9 of Planning to conduct a study and publish a comprehensive report on housing
10 infrastructure; requiring certain departments to conduct a comprehensive internal
11 review of certain approval processes that impact housing; and generally relating to
12 the oversight, regulation, development, and taxation and development of residential
13 real estate.
