6 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
7 INDICATED.
8 (2) “HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT” MEANS THE NEW
9 CONSTRUCTION OR SUBSTANTIAL RENOVATION OF A RESIDENTIAL REAL ESTATE
10 PROJECT.
11 (3) “HOUSING DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION” MEANS AN
12 APPLICATION FOR A BUILDING PERMIT, CERTIFICATION, AUTHORIZATION, SITE
13 PLAN APPROVAL, SUBDIVISION APPROVAL, CONCEPTUAL PLAN, OR ANY OTHER
14 DETERMINATION BY A LOCAL JURISDICTION RELATING TO A HOUSING
15 DEVELOPMENT PROJECT THAT HAS BEEN SUBMITTED TO A LOCAL JURISDICTION IN
16 COMPLIANCE WITH APPLICABLE REQUIREMENTS.
17 (B) AFTER MAKING A DETERMINATION THAT THERE IS A SHORTAGE OF
18 AFFORDABLE HOUSING IN A LOCAL JURISDICTION, THE GOVERNING BODY OF A
19 LOCAL JURISDICTION MAY ESTABLISH, BY LOCAL LAW, AN ADMINISTRATIVE
20 PROCESS TO REVIEW, APPROVE, MODIFY, OR DENY A HOUSING DEVELOPMENT
21 PROJECT APPLICATION.
22 (C) A LOCAL LAW THAT ESTABLISHES AN ADMINISTRATIVE PROCESS UNDER
23 SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION SHALL:
24 (1) DESIGNATE THE DEPARTMENT, OFFICIAL, OR STAFF THAT WILL
25 IMPLEMENT THE ADMINISTRATIVE PROCESS;
26 (2) PROVIDE THE PROCEDURES, CRITERIA, AND CONDITIONS FOR
27 THE ADMINISTRATIVE PROCESS;
28 (3) REQUIRE REASONABLE PUBLIC NOTICE AND OPPORTUNITY FOR
29 PUBLIC COMMENT DURING THE ADMINISTRATIVE PROCESS; AND
30 (4) ESTABLISH A PROCESS TO APPEAL A DECISION MADE THROUGH
31 THE ADMINISTRATIVE PROCESS.

