15 TITLE 12. HOUSING REGULATIONS, TARGETS, AND AFFORDABILITY.
16 SUBTITLE 1. DEFINITIONS.
17 12–101.
18 (A) IN THIS TITLE THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
19 INDICATED.
20 (B) “COMMISSION” MEANS THE MARYLAND–NATIONAL CAPITAL PARK AND
21 PLANNING COMMISSION.
22 (C) “COMPLETE APPLICATION” MEANS THE INITIAL SUBMITTAL OF AN
23 APPLICATION WITH ALL MATERIALS AND INFORMATION REQUIRED FOR
24 PROCESSING AND SUBSTANTIVE REVIEW AS DEFINED AND DETERMINED BY THE
25 LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION.
26 (D) “MIXED–USE” MEANS ANY COMBINATION OF A RESIDENTIAL USE WITH
27 RETAIL, COMMERCIAL, OFFICE, OR SERVICE USES IN THE SAME BUILDING OR ON

SENATE BILL 267 9
1 THE SAME SITE, WITH PERCENTAGES, DETERMINED BY THE LOCAL JURISDICTION
2 OR THE COMMISSION, ALLOCATED FOR EACH USE.
3 (E) “RESIDENTIAL” MEANS ANY USE APPROVED BY A LOCAL JURISDICTION
4 OR THE COMMISSION THAT IS FOR EXISTING OR PROPOSED DWELLING UNITS.
5 SUBTITLE 2. REGULATORY AND CONSTRUCTION CERTAINTY.
6 12–201.
7 THIS SUBTITLE APPLIES ONLY TO:
8 (1) A COUNTY WITH A POPULATION OF AT LEAST 150,000 RESIDENTS,
9 NOT INCLUDING ANY RESIDENTS OF A MUNICIPAL CORPORATION LOCATED WITHIN
10 THE COUNTY; AND
11 (2) A MUNICIPAL CORPORATION.
12 12–202.
13 (A) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, EACH LOCAL
14 JURISDICTION AND THE COMMISSION SHALL ESTABLISH A PROCESS TO EVALUATE
15 THE COMPLETENESS OF RESIDENTIAL OR MIXED–USE DEVELOPMENT PROJECT
16 APPLICATIONS.
17 (2) (I) WITHIN 30 DAYS AFTER RECEIPT OF A HOUSING
18 DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION, A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE
19 COMMISSION SHALL MAKE A DETERMINATION AS TO WHETHER THE APPLICATION IS
20 A COMPLETE APPLICATION.
21 (II) AFTER MAKING A DETERMINATION UNDER THIS
22 PARAGRAPH, THE LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION SHALL:
23 1. PROMPTLY NOTIFY THE APPLICANT OF THE
24 DETERMINATION AND THE DATE OF THE DETERMINATION; AND
25 2. IF THE LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION
26 HAS DETERMINED THAT THE APPLICATION IS NOT A COMPLETE APPLICATION,
27 PROVIDE THE APPLICANT WITH A LIST OF DEFICIENCIES AND A TIME FRAME FOR
28 CURING THE DEFICIENCIES.
29 (3) (I) IF DURING THE APPLICATION REVIEW PROCESS AN
30 APPLICANT FAILS TO RESPOND TO A REQUEST FROM A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE

10 SENATE BILL 267
1 COMMISSION FOR ADDITIONAL INFORMATION OR APPLICATION AMENDMENTS, THE
2 PROVISIONS OF SUBSECTIONS (B) AND (C) OF THIS SECTION DO NOT APPLY TO THE
3 APPLICATION.
4 (II) A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION SHALL
5 ESTABLISH THE TIME FRAME FOR RESPONSES REQUIRED UNDER THIS PARAGRAPH
6 BEFORE THE SUBMISSION OF THE APPLICATION.
7 (B) (1) FOR PURPOSES OF ESTABLISHING REGULATORY CERTAINTY,
8 AFTER VERIFICATION BY A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION THAT A
9 RESIDENTIAL OR MIXED–USE DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION IS COMPLETE,
10 AND FOR A PERIOD NOT TO EXCEED 3 YEARS UNLESS EXTENDED BY THE LOCAL
11 JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION:
12 (I) A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION SHALL
13 PROCESS AND REVIEW ANY APPLICATION FOR ZONING, SUBDIVISION, OR LAND
14 DEVELOPMENT APPROVAL USING THE LAND USE REGULATIONS, ZONING
15 ORDINANCES, AND DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS IN EFFECT ON THE DATE THE
16 APPLICATION IS VERIFIED TO BE COMPLETE; AND
17 (II) THE STATE MAY NOT IMPOSE NEW REGULATORY
18 DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS ON THE RESIDENTIAL OR MIXED–USE DEVELOPMENT
19 PROJECT APPLICATION.
20 (2) FOR PURPOSES OF THIS SUBSECTION, LOCAL REGULATIONS
21 ESTABLISHING IMPACT FEES OR DEVELOPMENT EXCISE TAXES MAY NOT BE
22 CONSIDERED LAND USE REGULATIONS, ZONING ORDINANCES, OR DEVELOPMENT
23 STANDARDS.
24 (C) FOR THE PURPOSE OF ESTABLISHING CONSTRUCTION CERTAINTY,
25 AFTER RECEIPT OF FINAL APPROVAL OF A RESIDENTIAL OR MIXED–USE
26 DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION BY A LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE
27 COMMISSION:
28 (1) THE LOCAL JURISDICTION OR THE COMMISSION MAY NOT IMPOSE
29 NEW DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS OR DOWNZONE LAND DURING THE APPROVAL
30 PERIOD OF THE DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION; AND
31 (2) THE LOCAL JURISDICTION, THE COMMISSION, OR THE STATE MAY
32 NOT IMPOSE NEW DEVELOPMENT STANDARDS DURING THE APPROVAL PERIOD OF
33 THE DEVELOPMENT PROJECT APPLICATION.
34 (D) NOTHING IN THIS SECTION MAY BE CONSTRUED TO:

