29 SUBTITLE 3. HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS.
30 12–301.

12 SENATE BILL 267
1 (A) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1, 2031, AND EACH JANUARY 1 FOLLOWING A
2 UNITED STATES DECENNIAL CENSUS THROUGH JANUARY 1, 2051, THE GOVERNOR
3 OR THE GOVERNOR’S DESIGNEE SHALL ESTABLISH HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS
4 FOR:
5 (1) THE STATE;
6 (2) EACH COUNTY; AND
7 (3) EACH MUNICIPAL CORPORATION THAT EXERCISES ZONING OR
8 PLANNING AUTHORITY.
9 (B) IN ESTABLISHING THE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS UNDER
10 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION, THE GOVERNOR SHALL:
11 (1) ANALYZE DATA AND FORECASTS RELATED TO:
12 (I) EMPLOYMENT DEMAND;
13 (II) HOUSING DEMAND;
14 (III) POPULATION GROWTH;
15 (IV) INFRASTRUCTURE CAPACITY AND CONSTRAINTS; AND
16 (V) ANY OTHER RELATED INFORMATION;
17 (2) CONSULT WITH EACH LOCAL JURISDICTION THAT MAY HAVE
18 HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS ESTABLISHED UNDER SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS
19 SECTION; AND
20 (3) CONSULT WITH THE COMMISSION ABOUT HOUSING PRODUCTION
21 TARGETS THAT MAY BE ESTABLISHED WITHIN THE COMMISSION’S JURISDICTION.
22 (C) THE GOVERNOR SHALL:
23 (1) REEVALUATE AND REVISE THE ESTABLISHED HOUSING
24 PRODUCTION TARGETS; AND
25 (2) IN CONSULTATION WITH THE MARYLAND ASSOCIATION OF
26 COUNTIES AND THE MARYLAND MUNICIPAL LEAGUE, DEVELOP METRICS TO
27 MEASURE THE PROGRESS TOWARD THE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS.

SENATE BILL 267 13
1 (D) (1) THE GOVERNOR SHALL PUBLISH THE CURRENT HOUSING
2 PRODUCTION TARGETS ESTABLISHED UNDER THIS SECTION ON THE GOVERNOR’S
3 WEBSITE AND NOTIFY EACH APPLICABLE LOCAL JURISDICTION AND THE
4 COMMISSION OF THE TARGETS IN A TIMELY MANNER.
5 (2) THE PUBLICATION UNDER THIS SUBSECTION SHALL PROVIDE A
6 SUPPORTING BASIS FOR THE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS THAT ARE
7 ESTABLISHED.
8 (3) WITHIN 1 MONTH AFTER THE PUBLICATION OF HOUSING
9 PRODUCTION TARGETS, THE GOVERNOR SHALL SUBMIT, IN ACCORDANCE WITH §
10 2–1257 OF THE STATE GOVERNMENT ARTICLE, A REPORT ON THE INFORMATION
11 PUBLISHED REGARDING HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS TO THE GENERAL
12 ASSEMBLY.
13 (E) (1) ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1 FOLLOWING PUBLICATION OF THE
14 HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS AND ON OR BEFORE JANUARY 1 EACH YEAR
15 THEREAFTER, THE GOVERNOR SHALL PUBLISH A REPORT THAT:
16 (I) IDENTIFIES THE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS FOR THE
17 STATE AND EACH LOCAL JURISDICTION;
18 (II) ASSESSES THE CUMULATIVE PROGRESS AND THE PROGRESS
19 FOR THE PRIOR YEAR OF THE STATE AND EACH LOCAL JURISDICTION TOWARD
20 MEETING APPLICABLE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGETS USING THE METRICS
21 DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (C)(2) OF THIS SECTION;
22 (III) FOR ANY HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGET THAT THE
23 GOVERNOR DETERMINES IS NOT PRACTICABLY MEASURED BY THE METRICS
24 DEVELOPED UNDER SUBSECTION (C)(2) OF THIS SECTION, INCLUDES AN
25 EXPLANATION THAT THE HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGET MAY NOT BE PRACTICABLY
26 MEASURED AND A DESCRIPTION OF THE STATUS TOWARD ACHIEVING THE HOUSING
27 PRODUCTION TARGET; AND
28 (IV) PROVIDES A SUPPORTING BASIS FOR ANY ALTERATION TO
29 AN ESTABLISHED HOUSING PRODUCTION TARGET.
30 (2) (I) THE GOVERNOR SHALL PUBLISH THE REPORT ON THE
31 GOVERNOR’S WEBSITE AND NOTIFY EACH APPLICABLE LOCAL JURISDICTION AND
32 THE COMMISSION OF THE REPORT IN A TIMELY MANNER.
33 (II) WITHIN 1 MONTH AFTER THE PUBLICATION OF THE REPORT
34 REQUIRED IN PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION, THE GOVERNOR SHALL SUBMIT

