3 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That:
4 (a) (1) The Department of Planning shall conduct a study and publish a
5 comprehensive report on housing infrastructure to assess how existing and planned
6 infrastructure systems support or constrain housing development across the State.
7 (2) The comprehensive report on housing infrastructure shall be organized
8 into the following four primary parts:
9 (i) water and sewer infrastructure;
10 (ii) school facility capacity;
11 (iii) transportation infrastructure; and
12 (iv) policy recommendations.
13 (b) (1) The water and sewer infrastructure part of the report shall:
14 (i) evaluate the interrelationship between current and projected
15 housing development patterns and the availability, condition, and capacity of water and
16 wastewater infrastructure; and
17 (ii) include an analysis of:
18 1. existing public water and sewer service areas, including
19 coverage gaps;
20 2. capacity constraints of wastewater treatment plants;
21 3. the availability and sustainability of private wells;
22 4. the use and environmental impact of septic systems; and
23 5. the age, condition, and maintenance needs of water and
24 sewer infrastructure.
25 (2) The Department of Planning shall consult and coordinate with the
26 following entities in developing the water and sewer infrastructure part of the report:
27 (i) the Department of Environment;
28 (ii) the Maryland Department of Health;

